<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="60" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/1825: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Counselor of Embassy in China</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Peck</hi></persName>),
                                    <hi rend="italic">at Chungking</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-29T18:00:00-04:00">May 29, 1939—6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>97. Department’s 90, May 19, 6 p.m., last paragraph, and your 341,
                                May 23, 10 a.m. On May 29 an officer of the Department took this
                                matter up with the Chinese Ambassador here and gave him a copy of
                                our text of the <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> which you
                                delivered to the Minister for Foreign Affairs on May 22.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Peiping and Shanghai.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>